SIMPLE: posterity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Posterity
<hw>Pos*ter"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>posteritas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>post⟦eacute⟧rit⟦eacute⟧</ets>. See
<er>Posterior</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The race that proceeds from
a progenitor; offspring to the furthest generation; the aggregate number
of persons who are descended from an ancestor of a generation;
descendants; -- contrasted with <xex>ancestry</xex>; <as>as, the
<ex>posterity</ex> of Abraham</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If [the crown] should not stand in thy <qex>posterity</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Succeeding generations; future times.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Their names shall be transmitted to <qex>posterity</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Their names shall be transmitted to <qex>posterity</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Smalridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Postern</ent>⟦br⟧
